<br>
What I don't, and I guess will never get is when my Storyteller for one game in particular told us that dying was a natural part of the gaming process. Okay??? Sure, in D&amp;D you can get a body resurected, is this what most players look foreward to? No. ( was not the same ST as my good games ) Why plan adventures that require your players to decide who is going to kick it before they go off into the wilderness? Seriously. Bah, I just want a good game where I can put the personality behind my character into play. I enjoy making slightly off the wall characters, why give them that extra spark if no one is going to appreciate it?<br>
<br>
So far my favorite ones have been my Dwarven Bard and my Aesimar Cleric of Corellion Latheren ( sp? I don't care it's way too late to look it up now ).  Both started off on Faerun, although the Cleric moved onto a Spelljammer environment. <br>
<br>
What I want to know is, am I the only one who has problems finding a compatible gaming group? I don't want Rollplay, I want Roleplay.  Does anyone else have this problem? Or additionally the problem of: &quot; Erm, you're roleplaying that exactly like -blank- from - blank movie/book/etc.- . If I wanted to play with Duncan from Highlander or the Crow I suppose I'd play in that setting. What's with that?? &quot;  * sighs * Sorry pet peeve. <br>
