<br>
My three favorite Tabletop games would be D&amp;D3e, Rolemaster/MERP, and the WW Storytellers system.<br>
<br>
What I look for in gaming is, like mentioned above, mature players that know how to weave a proper story. If they arent creative, then maturity doesnt help them. I have many nights where we will play 6-8 hours and not have a single combat and minimal skill rolling. I prefer hardcore RP to combat.<br>
<br>
Another thing I look for is a willingness to work with others to weave that said story. Its a group project and needs everyones imput to make it truly epic. <br>
<br>
I would also prefer it if people had the ability to RP something that conflicts with their RL selves. I cant stand it when Im running a good game because noone feels that Lawful Good is a cool alignment. Thats D00Dism to me. They wanna be the bad-ass good-guy. Thats fine, but not ALL THE TIME! <br>
<br>
Heh.<br>
<br>
No idea if I answered your questions.<br>
